docs.abstract: The outgoing White House chief of staff’s comments come as a partial government shutdown caused by a fight over a border barrier drags into a second week.
docs.snippet: The outgoing White House chief of staff’s comments come as a partial government shutdown caused by a fight over a border barrier drags into a second week.
docs.lead_paragraph: The concrete border wall that President Trump has repeatedly called for as a signature campaign promise is not actually a wall and has not been since “early on in the administration,” the outgoing White House chief of staff, John F. Kelly, said in an interview published Sunday.

headline.main: Kelly, on His Way Out, Says Administration Long Ago Abandoned Idea of Concrete Wall
headline.print_headline: Kelly Says Administration  Long Ago Gave Up on Wall

docs.abstract: The case of a New Hampshire man raises questions about criminal libel laws, which about half of states have and under which prosecutions are not uncommon.
docs.snippet: The case of a New Hampshire man raises questions about criminal libel laws, which about half of states have and under which prosecutions are not uncommon.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Like lots of Americans, Robert Frese is not shy about expressing his views on the internet. Last year, in a comment on a newspaper’s Facebook page, he said a New Hampshire police officer who had given him a traffic citation was “a dirty cop.” The police chief, Mr. Frese added, was a coward who had covered up the matter.

headline.main: He Disparaged the Police on Facebook. So They Arrested Him.
headline.print_headline: He Criticized the Police Online. So They Arrested Him.

docs.abstract: The White House said Monday that Ms. Liang, an expert on financial regulation, had decided not to seek a seat on the Federal Reserve’s board.
docs.snippet: The White House said Monday that Ms. Liang, an expert on financial regulation, had decided not to seek a seat on the Federal Reserve’s board.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The White House said Monday that Nellie Liang, an economist and financial regulation expert nominated by President Trump for a seat on the Federal Reserve’s board of governors, had withdrawn her name from consideration.

headline.main: Fed Nominee Nellie Liang Withdraws From Consideration

docs.abstract: The Democratic leaders dismissed the president’s address making a case for a border wall as riddled with misinformation and fear-mongering.
docs.snippet: The Democratic leaders dismissed the president’s address making a case for a border wall as riddled with misinformation and fear-mongering.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Democratic congressional leaders called on President Trump on Tuesday to reopen the federal government while they resolve differences with him over securing the southern border, in a formal response to his prime-time address from the Oval Office that they dismissed as riddled with misinformation and fear-mongering.

headline.main: Schumer and Pelosi, Responding to Trump’s Speech, Call to Reopen Government

docs.abstract: President Trump’s threat to invoke emergency powers to build a border wall would be extraordinarily aggressive and most likely touch off a legal battle.
docs.snippet: President Trump’s threat to invoke emergency powers to build a border wall would be extraordinarily aggressive and most likely touch off a legal battle.
docs.lead_paragraph: Updated February 14, 2019: Senator Mitch McConnell, the majority leader, announced that President Trump planned to declare a national emergency so he can bypass Congress and build his long-promised wall along the southwestern border. Read the latest here.

headline.main: National Emergency Powers and Trump’s Border Wall, Explained
headline.print_headline: How Trump Might Claim Emergency To Get Wall

docs.abstract: Candidates are pledging to protect pre-existing conditions, a stance often at odds with their votes, but their leaders are vowing to revisit an Affordable Care Act repeal.
docs.snippet: Candidates are pledging to protect pre-existing conditions, a stance often at odds with their votes, but their leaders are vowing to revisit an Affordable Care Act repeal.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — In advertisements, in debates and on the campaign trail, Republican candidates are abandoning their promise to “repeal and replace” the Affordable Care Act and are swearing that they never voted to undo protections for people with pre-existing medical conditions — and never will.

headline.main: Republican Candidates Soften Tone on Health Care as Their Leaders Dig In
headline.print_headline: G.O.P. Candidates Soften Stance on Affordable Care Act as Leaders Dig In

docs.abstract: In a decision that could further damage President Trump’s image, Mr. Cohen will give “a full and credible account” of his work for Mr. Trump next month before the House Oversight Committee.
docs.snippet: In a decision that could further damage President Trump’s image, Mr. Cohen will give “a full and credible account” of his work for Mr. Trump next month before the House Oversight Committee.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Michael D. Cohen, President Trump’s former personal lawyer who implicated him in a scheme to pay hush money to two women claiming to have had affairs with him, said on Thursday that he had agreed to testify before a House committee next month and give “a full and credible account” of his work for Mr. Trump.

headline.main: Michael Cohen, Trump’s Former Lawyer, Agrees to Testify to Congress
headline.print_headline: Lawyer Who Arranged Hush Money for Trump Will Testify to Congress

docs.abstract: President Trump is considering building a barrier without congressional authorization, but it is not clear that such a step could withstand court scrutiny.
docs.snippet: President Trump is considering building a barrier without congressional authorization, but it is not clear that such a step could withstand court scrutiny.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Trump raised the possibility on Friday of declaring a national emergency to allow him to build a wall along the southwest border without congressional approval, hours after Department of Homeland Security officials requested additional support to erect temporary barriers between the United States and Mexico.

headline.main: Trump Raises Possibility of Declaring National Emergency at Border
headline.print_headline: Trump Suggests Declaring National Emergency to Skirt Congress on Wall

byline.original: By Glenn Thrush and Thomas Gibbons-Neff

docs.abstract: The overall number of guests affected by the hacking, in which Chinese intelligence is the leading suspect, declined to 383 million. But the passport data is critical to intelligence agencies.
docs.snippet: The overall number of guests affected by the hacking, in which Chinese intelligence is the leading suspect, declined to 383 million. But the passport data is critical to intelligence agencies.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Marriott International said on Friday that the biggest hacking of personal information in history was not quite as big as first feared, but for the first time conceded that its Starwood hotel unit did not encrypt the passport numbers for roughly five million guests. Those passport numbers were lost in an attack that many outside experts believe was carried out by Chinese intelligence agencies.

headline.main: Marriott Concedes 5 Million Passport Numbers Lost to Hackers Were Not Encrypted
headline.print_headline: Marriott Says Millions of Hacked Passport Numbers Weren’t Encrypted

docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Congress is reviewing the Trump administration’s decision to lift sanctions on companies owned by Oleg V. Deripaska, an influential Russian oligarch with close ties to President Vladimir V. Putin, Democrats said on Friday.

headline.main: Congress Is Examining Decision to Lift Sanctions on Russian’s Firms
